<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3269] ACTIVEMQ_OPTS_MEMORY is ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3269</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have just realised that my brokers were running with 256M of ram, which given they used to operate on 512M raised concerns. Checking my /etc/default/activemq file I do have:&lt;br/&gt;
ACTIVEMQ_OPTS_MEMORY=&quot;-Xms512M -Xmx512M&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I echo out the result of ACTIVEMQ_OPTS within the init.d script (linked to /opt/activemq/bin/activemq) I see only the default 256M resolved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only way I was able to up the limit was by editing the init script and replacing the default value with my own.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Marking this as a regression as I am 99% sure this was working in 5.4.x.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
